I live nearby and everytime I visit this coffee shop, I have the worst experience. The coffee here is not good, the food is terrible, and the staff is incredibly rude. It has an $8 minimum to use a credit card for a coffee shop. Last time, I went in the cashier had a full conversation with his friend in front of me for 5 min, while I waited and gave him a free coffee, Once I ordered my latte, did not tell me that there was a minimum as the sign was turned and I could not read it. So, after my latte was made and the cashier rang me up, told me about the minimum and I did not have cash and had to order a $6 fruit and yogurt cup. I spent $10. The next time I went in knowingly ordered a drip coffee and fruit and yogurt cup to go. After I walked home in the cold, I opened it and was only given a fruit cup. When I called they and told them, they were defensive and said that's what we heard, instead of apologizing for the mistake. My boyfriend also has had terrible experiences at this coffee shop. Do not visit or support this coffee shop.

Unfortunately, the women behind the counter was quite rude. I was on the phone when I came in, but was being relatively quiet and respectful.  After I bought a coffee and sat down, she gestured that I was disturbing people and I should leave. If there was an issue, she should have first addressed it and mentioned that I was being too loud (which wasn't the case) and she could have asked me to take it outside if it was a real problem. But instead, she was just rude and obnoxious. I live in the area, love supporting local businesses, but I do not think that I will be going back.
